com.launchdarkly.sdk

Class EvaluationReason

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.launchdarkly.sdk.EvaluationReason
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    EvaluationReason.Error, EvaluationReason.Fallthrough, EvaluationReason.Off, EvaluationReason.PrerequisiteFailed, EvaluationReason.RuleMatch, EvaluationReason.TargetMatch

    public abstract class EvaluationReason
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes the reason that a flag evaluation produced a particular value.

    This is returned within EvaluationDetail by the SDK's "variation detail" methods such as boolVariationDetail.

    Note that this is an enum-like class hierarchy rather than an enum, because some of the possible reasons have their own properties.

    Since:
    4.3.0

      Subclass of EvaluationReason that indicates that the flag was off and therefore returned its configured off value.
      static class  EvaluationReason.PrerequisiteFailed
      Subclass of EvaluationReason that indicates that the flag was considered off because it had at least one prerequisite flag that either was off or did not return the desired variation.
      static class  EvaluationReason.RuleMatch
      Subclass of EvaluationReason that indicates that the user matched one of the flag's rules.
      static class  EvaluationReason.TargetMatch
      Subclass of EvaluationReason that indicates that the user key was specifically targeted for this flag.
